Terraform Learning Summary
Project context: Banaras Dairy app ke liye AWS S3 bucket, IAM policy, IAM user, access key Terraform se create kiya.

Terraform ka purpose samjha:

Infrastructure ko code ke through create/manage karna.
Manual AWS Console steps ko repeatable .tf files me convert karna.
Provider concept samjha:

Provider ek plugin/library hota hai jo Terraform ko AWS APIs se baat karna sikhata hai.
terraform init command provider download karta hai .terraform/ directory me.
AWS provider source use kiya: hashicorp/aws.
terraform {} block aur provider "aws" {} block ka difference samjha:

terraform {} block provider source/version define karta hai.
provider "aws" {} block AWS region/profile define karta hai.
Region use kiya: ap-south-1.
Profile use kiya: banaras-dairy-deployer.
Version pinning samjha:

version = "~> 5.0" ka use kiya.
Iska matlab AWS provider version 5.x allow hoga, lekin 6.x nahi.
Reason: future breaking changes se bachna.
AWS credentials handling samjha:

Hardcoded credentials .tf file me nahi rakhna.
Local development ke liye named AWS CLI profile use karna best hai.
CI/CD me environment variables use hote hain.
AWS production resources pe IAM Role best approach hai.
HCL syntax samjha:

Terraform me comma nahi lagta.
String values quotes me hoti hain.
Resource references quotes ke bina hoti hain.
Example:
"banaras-dairy-app" = direct string
aws_iam_user.user.name = resource reference
Map vs List samjha:

{} map ke liye hota hai, key-value pair:
tags = { Project = "BanarasDairy" }
[] list ke liye hota hai:
Action = ["s3:PutObject", "s3:GetObject"]
S3 resource create karna sikha:

resource "aws_s3_bucket" "bills_bucket" use kiya.
Bucket name: banaras-dairy-bills.
IAM policy create karna sikha:

aws_iam_policy resource use kiya.
jsonencode() se IAM policy JSON likhna sikha.
Least privilege actions use kiye:
s3:PutObject
s3:GetObject
s3:DeleteObject
S3 ARN difference samjha:

arn:aws:s3:::bucket-name bucket ke liye hota hai.
arn:aws:s3:::bucket-name/* bucket ke andar objects ke liye hota hai.
Object operations ke liye /* zaroori hai.
IAM user create karna sikha:

aws_iam_user resource use kiya.
User: banaras-dairy-app.
IAM policy attachment sikha:

aws_iam_user_policy_attachment use kiya.
Policy ko IAM user se attach kiya.
Access key Terraform se create karna sikha:

aws_iam_access_key resource use kiya.
Access Key ID output me dikh sakta hai.
Secret key sensitive output hota hai.
Output block samjha:

output block Terraform values terminal me show karne ke liye hota hai.
Secret output ke liye sensitive = true use kiya.
Secret nikalne ke liye:
terraform output -raw app_secret_access_key
Terraform commands sikhe:

terraform init provider download/init ke liye.
terraform plan dry run ke liye.
terraform apply actual AWS resource create/update/delete ke liye.
terraform plan vs terraform apply samjha:

plan sirf batata hai kya hoga.
apply actual changes karta hai AWS me.
State file concept clear hua:

terraform.tfstate Terraform ka memory/notebook hai.
Terraform resources ko local resource name se track karta hai.
State file delete karne se Terraform resources bhool jata hai.
State file delete hone ka impact samjha:

AWS resources delete nahi hote.
Resources orphan ho jate hain.
Terraform unko manage nahi kar pata.
Recovery ke liye terraform import use hota hai.
.terraform.lock.hcl samjha:

Exact provider version lock karta hai.
Is file ko Git me commit karna chahiye.
.terraform/ folder samjha:

Provider binaries store hoti hain.
Isko Git me commit nahi karna.
terraform.tfstate.backup samjha:

Previous state ka backup hota hai.
Isko Git me commit nahi karna.
.gitignore rule samjha:

Commit nahi karna:
.terraform/
terraform.tfstate
terraform.tfstate.backup
*.tfvars
Commit karna:
.tf files
.terraform.lock.hcl
Idempotency samjha:

Agar resource already Terraform state me hai aur .tf me same hai, Terraform usko touch nahi karta.
Sirf changed resource pe action leta hai.
Local resource name ka importance samjha:

Terraform AWS resource ko local name se track karta hai.
Example: aws_s3_bucket.bills_bucket.
Agar local name change kar diya, Terraform old resource ko deleted aur new resource ko created samjhega.
Bucket name change behavior samjha:

S3 bucket name immutable hota hai.
Bucket name change karne par Terraform old bucket destroy karke new bucket create karega.
Same file me multiple resources banana samjha:

Agar second bucket chahiye, existing resource block edit nahi karna.
New resource block add karna:
aws_s3_bucket.bills_bucket
aws_s3_bucket.photos_bucket
moved block concept samjha:

Local resource rename karte waqt destroy/create avoid karne ke liye use hota hai.
Example:
moved {
  from = aws_s3_bucket.bills_bucket
  to   = aws_s3_bucket.new_bills_bucket
}
lifecycle block concept samjha:

prevent_destroy = true use karke important resources accidental delete se bachaye ja sakte hain.
Useful for S3 buckets, RDS, production stateful resources.
terraform import concept samjha:

Existing AWS resource ko Terraform state me bring karne ke liye use hota hai.
Useful when resource manually created ho ya state delete ho gaya ho.
Real-world project structure samjha:

Ek bada demo1.tf chal sakta hai, lekin production me split karna better hai:
provider.tf
s3.tf
iam.tf
outputs.tf
variables.tf
Infrastructure vs application deployment ka difference samjha:

Terraform infrastructure create/manage karta hai.
CI/CD app deploy karta hai.
Dono ko usually separate pipeline/process me rakhna chahiye.
